The paper deals with the issue of human-AI collaboration, which is a common topic in the field of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). It also addresses the problem of human perception and understanding of AI behavior, which falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The domains of autonomous cars and physical robots suggest that the paper may also be relevant to the fields of robotics (cs.RO) and control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper uses regression models and search algorithms, which are common techniques in machine learning (cs.LG).
